qualityControlLevel.explanation: Raw and unprocessed data and data products that have not undergone quality control. Depending on the variable, data type, and data transmission system, raw data may be available within seconds or minutes after the measurements have been made. Examples include real time precipitation, streamflow and water quality measurements.

method.methodDescription: Turbidity measured using a Forest Technology Systems DTS-12 turbidity sensor.

metadata.title: Little Bear River Conservation Effects Assessment Project water quality data.
metadata.abstract: Under funding from the United States Department of Agricultures Conservations Effects Assessment program, USU is conducting continuous water quality monitoring of the Little Bear River to demonstrate and compare the use of alternative monitoring approaches in estimating pollutant concentrations and loads.

source.citation: Continuous water quality monitoring by Jeff Horsburgh, David Stevens, Nancy Mesner and others from Utah State University as part of the USDA Conservation Effects Assessment Grant
